content: Overall a pretty good representative example of actual test. FSC is twenty questions not the 10 used here. Overall questions are accurate however Photos diagrams are difficult to see. Pretty good comprehensive answers and explanations. It is free and that what works.

There are several misleading, convoluted questions that do not test ones knowledge of the subject matter. These do a disservice to the to the student and others who benefit from properly taught individuals.
Too many questions that are NOT on the FSC test
The material was okay..but the actaul test had questions not covered by this app.
Bad. Alot of the questions on here arent even on the study guid book. How am i suppose to know a question when the book does not even cover the tipic of the question. Afwul.

Pretty straightforward app, just kept taking the quizzes for about an hour, got 100% on my FSC Test the same day and it took me 5 minutes to finish. It would be better if it pulled new questions each test, sometimes I would get a majority of the same questions. Some questions in these quizzes were overkill (I had version 2 of the test and none of the picture questions were on it) but it helps to give more knowledge in general which I don't mind, but maybe have these in a separate quiz.

Overall, quite satisfied with the app. I would have been blind-sighted by the test questions that ask details about ammo type and use, as well as some others that are never mentioned at all in the official CA study guide. My main complaint is that the pictures are so small and can't be enlarged, it is sometimes very hard or impossible to tell which part of a weapon (especially on black pistols) is pointed at or whether a grip is good.
This app has questions on it that aren't covered in the FSC handbook with no explanation of the answers. The pictures are too small and too dark to make out details.
Passed ca test with this as study guide 6/6/2020

Passed the exam with flying colors with this app and studying up on the FSC study guide. This practice exam definitely offers more content and detail than the actual test itself, but it offered me more insight and a deeper knowledge of gun safety. This allowed me to use the actual study guide more as a reference point to better understand the questions. I highly recommend this app.

I just downloaded and read the manual for DOJ California. I've taken all their practice test and passed with 100% on all 5 chapters. Many questions here do not reflect the answers that the DOJ looks for. Example - you can make your answer deemed right by the DOJ handbook but this app will consider your answer incorrect. Maybe this app needs to update according to the DOJ standards for the state of California. As of right now this app will throw you off if you have read the DOJ manual.
replyContent: Hi Joey, thank you very much for your feedback. We strive to make the app better and we will definitely fix the discrepancies. Could you please give an example of the particular question or answer, which contradicts to the DOJ standards/handbook or seems confusing? At least approximately. That would help a lot, thank you!

content: I passed

It might be ok as a study tool, but it's rather unprofessionally developed. Many of the questions and answers had grammar and spelling mistakes, and some of them relied on picture references which couldn't be reliably interpreted. Definitely not worth the price.

Two questions in their practice test are flat out wrong and I knew it but answered them on the test the way practice test had them anyway and got two wrong on the actual test because this product I paid for wasnt properly gone through before release. Even the DOJ website itself isnt up to date on the laws pertaining to those two questions. That's pretty unprofessional. The question about gun buying age and what line of safety is a safety were both botched in practice test and differ from actual.

Great Study Guide! Just passed my test with flying colors. Would have got 100 on my test but one question has not been updated yet. New law in California as of January 1, 2019 states you must be 21 to buy a rifle. Was 18 years of age. I'll take 29 out of 30. Thanks again. A good investment if you plan to purchase any firearms in California.
Great app, has all the info you need to pass the test. I was able to pass on the first try with all 30 questions correct.
It would be nice if you can enlarge the photos so you can see the writing on them but other than that it's a very useful app
This app should have an option to study 300+ questions instead of going through them randomly.
replyContent: Hello Brian, such option exists: go to the menu (3 dots on top right) - Settings  -  set Training mode. This will make questions in quizzes to appear one by one, and you will be able to cover them all without random test generation. Hope this will help. Good luck with your FSC and let us know if any other problems.

content: Lol this test is definitely not the same as what is actually given and in fact is much harder than the test.  Still going thru it gives you a thorough knowledge to easily pass the test
It worked well for my husband, purchased it for him. He found it useful.

Gets the job done! Pretty good!  It does what is supposed to do, simple and straightforward. You might find some minor spelling issues, otherwise – good work. It would be great to have quizzes by topics like bare minimum, hunting, etc.
This is too granular. While it may be good information it is not what's on the test. Misleading.
replyContent: Dear customer! Our application is based on the latest test preparation materials. All changes to test questions are transferred to the app in timely manner. However we CANNOT guarantee the test questions and the app to have the exact wording of questions and answers. The app focuses on how to apply the basic principles to any situation you may face
